cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource allocation in multi-user cognitive radio networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes optimal resource allocation algorithms to enhance the spectral efficiency of the network, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Cognitive radio networks involve sharing of spectrum with primary users, which requires secure communication protocols. The paper may touch upon security aspects of the network. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes algorithms to optimize the resource allocation in the network, which involves control systems and optimization techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper evaluates the performance of the network in terms of average spectral efficiency, which may be related to multimedia applications that require high data rates.
